The most probable token has a probability mass of 0.2. The next 4 most probable tokens each have a probability mass of 0.1, so their cumulative probability mass is 0.6. The next 20 most probable tokens each have a probability mass of 0.01, so their cumulative probability mass is 0.8. This means that the set of tokens we need to sample from includes the most probable token, the next 4 most probable tokens, and the next 20 most probable tokens. 

Therefore, the set of tokens we need to sample from includes 1 + 4 + 20 = 25 tokens.

