int old_values[] = {1, 2, 3, 4};
int new_values[] = {5, 6, 7, 8};

if (compare_and_swap(arr, old_values, new_values, 4)) {
    // The compare-and-swap was successful, arr now contains [5, 6, 7, 8]
} else {
    // The compare-and-swap failed, arr still contains [1, 2, 3, 4]
}
```

If we try to update the array with old values `[1, 2, 3, 5]` instead, the compare-and-swap will fail because the fourth value in the array is different from the expected value:

